<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 1 KILLED, 1 HOSPITALIZED IN PACOIMA BAR FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man was stabbed to death and another was critically wounded during a 
late-night melee at a bar near San Fernando Road and Branford Street in 
Pacoima, Los Angeles police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Officer Robert Nowak said police found the dead victim Saturday about 11:30 
p.m., lying in the street outside 9980 San Fernando Road with stab wounds in 
the upper torso. 
</P>
<P>
The second victim was found about a block away with similar wounds. He was 
taken to Northridge Hospital Medical Center, where he was reported in critical 
condition Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Nowak said the stabbings evidently occurred during a bar brawl. The names of 
the victims were being withheld pending notification of their relatives, he 
said. 
</P>
