<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PALMDALE MAN STABBED, ROBBED BEHIND MARKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 36-year-old Palmdale man was stabbed three times and robbed of $80 as he 
walked down an alley behind a supermarket, Los Angeles County sheriff's 
deputies said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Jones was stabbed twice in the chest and once in the back in the attack, 
which occurred about 8 p.m. Saturday behind a Lucky supermarket at Palmdale 
Boulevard and 25th Street East, said Deputy Wayne Kiger. Jones was taken to 
Palmdale Hospital Medical Center, where he was treated and released, Kiger 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The attacker also hit Jones over the head before going through his pockets and 
escaping with the money, Kiger said. 
</P>
<P>
No arrests have been made in connection with the incident. 
