<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHALLENGES TO PROPOSITION 13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We moved here just after the passage of Prop. 13 and bought a home in Los 
Angeles. I was amazed that nobody seemed to realize that the new tax break for 
homeowners discriminated against us new owners. 
</P>
<P>
But then, who cared about new buyers -- buying at inflated prices -- as long as 
the original settlers kept their status quo. 
</P>
<P>
Of course, the tax rate should stay at 1%, but all property should be appraised 
equally. I cannot understand why it should be such an issue. Equality is so 
easy to comprehend. 
</P>
<P>
For those financially strapped senior citizens who would find it difficult to 
pay a fair share of the taxes, there is a state program which permits them to 
withhold all property taxes until the house is sold. 
</P>
<P>
Since my tax base is different from that of people who purchased their homes 
before 1978, I feel that we are being discriminated against -- most unfairly. 
</P>
<P>
NATALIE MILLER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
