<HEADLINE>
<P>
ESTRADA TO DEFEND WBA TITLE AGAINST SAN DIEGO'S SALUD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALLAN MALAMUD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Forum, better known for basketball and hockey, will present its ninth world 
championship boxing match of the year tonight when Juan Jose (Dinamita) Estrada 
of Tijuana defends his World Boxing Assn. junior featherweight title against 
Jesus Salud of San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The bout, scheduled for 12 rounds, twice has been postponed because of a cut 
lip Estrada suffered in training in October. 
</P>
<P>
Estrada (36-7, 30 knockouts) is favored to make a fourth successful defense of 
the title he won on a split decision over Bernardo Pinango last year. Since 
then, he has stopped Takuya Muguruma and Jesus Poll and decisioned Luis 
Mendoza. 
</P>
<P>
Salud (31-3, 16 knockouts), the seventh-ranked contender at 122 pounds, was 
born in the Philippines and began his career in Hawaii, where he won his first 
18 fights. He is best known at the Forum for his 10th-round loss to Frankie 
Duarte in a bloody slugfest three years ago. 
</P>
<P>
The undercard includes a 12-rounder between Edgar Castro and Manuel Medina for 
the vacant WBA intercontinental super-featherweight title. That bout begins at 
7 p.m. and will be followed by the main event. ALLAN MALAMUD 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121189-0028 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 146764 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 11, 1989, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
