<P>
BALTIC RADICALS WINNING POSTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TALLINN, Soviet Union 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Radical groups in Estonia and Latvia demanding a return to their Baltic 
republics' prewar independence looked set for substantial gains from weekend 
local elections. 
</P>
<P>
Preliminary results today in the Estonian capital of Tallinn showed a 12-member 
radical alliance had picked up 18 of the 80 City Council seats after preference 
votes were counted and was likely to win at least 40 when the final tally was 
calculated. Among the 18 was a member of the environmentalist Greens Party. 
</P>
<P>
A complex preferential voting system means the full outcome will not be known 
for several days. 
</P>
