<TEXT>
<P>
Sixteen blacks were killed and 65 homes destroyed in one of the worst outbreaks 
of violence during three years of factional fighting in Natal province, police 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
Also Sunday, four blacks were killed, eight were injured and more than 100 
homes were razed in arson attacks related to a power struggle in the Crossroads 
shantytown outside Cape Town, fire and hospital officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The most serious violence Sunday was in the Ntuzuma township near the Indian 
Ocean city of Durban, where 11 people died and 45 homes were burned, according 
to the report. It said those killed were either attacked by rampaging mobs or 
shot by police trying to disperse the crowds. 
