<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; 
</P>
<P>
HOTEL, OFFICE PROJECTS AWAIT COUNCIL VOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Major decisions on two of Garden Grove's biggest redevelopment projects, a 
downtown office-retail complex and a three-story hotel, are expected at 
tonight's City Council meeting. The office-retail project would be at the 
northwest corner of Garden Grove Boulevard and Euclid Street, an 8.5-acre site 
which has been vacant for nearly a decade. 
</P>
<P>
IDM of Long Beach would build a five-story office building and several 
one-story retail and office structures. Construction would begin in January, 
1991. 
</P>
<P>
The council also is scheduled to vote on La Quinta Inns' plan to build a 
three-story, 168-room hotel on a 2.8-acre site at the northwest corner of 
Garden Grove Boulevard and Haster Street. 
</P>
</TEXT>
