<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
MAN SUFFERS FATAL CUT IN BAR FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 22-year-old man was fatally injured Sunday morning when his throat was 
slashed during a fight that started inside the Red Turtle Bar and spilled out 
into a parking lot, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
Despite efforts to save him, Pedro Ramon Miranda of Santa Ana died of his 
injuries at Fountain Valley Regional Hospital and Medical Center, Santa Ana 
Police Sgt. Jim McDaniel said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the fight started about 1:30 a.m. inside the Red Turtle Bar at 1019 
S. Fairview St. During the melee, someone cut Miranda across the throat with a 
knife and fled, McDaniel said. When paramedics arrived, Miranda was near death 
from loss of blood. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses told police that they saw a man carrying a knife running from the 
parking lot. They described him as between the ages of 20 and 24, 5 feet, 6 
inches tall and having a slender build, and that he was wearing a white 
T-shirt. 
</P>
<P>
"This happened in a real difficult neighborhood," McDaniel said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
