<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO NADADORES QUALIFY FOR SWIM NATIONALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two 16-year-old Mission Viejo Nadadores swimmers, Eric Diehl and Ryan Cox, 
qualified for the U.S. Senior Nationals in the 1,650-yard freestyle event 
Sunday at Belmont Plaza Pool in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Diehl won the race in 15 minutes 37.87 seconds and Cox followed in 15:40.92. 
The qualifying standard for the Senior Nationals, to be held in Nashville in 
March, is 15:45.39. Earlier in the invitational, which started Thursday, Diehl 
had qualified for the Senior Nationals in the 1,000-, 500- and 200-yard 
freestyle events. 
</P>
<P>
Diehl and Cox were the only swimmers to qualify for the senior event, which 
will serve as the trials for the Goodwill Games in Seattle in 1990. Earlier in 
the competition Amy Ward of the Southern California Aquatics Club in Tustin 
qualified in the 1,000-, 500- and 200-yard free events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
